# [NMOP](../wg/nmop.html)

## Summary

The Network Management Operations (NMOP) Working Group held its first session at IETF 126. The session covered the status of active working group documents, dependencies with external working group drafts, and specific presentations on YANG-push to message broker integration, network anomaly detection, network incident management, and CMOP/SIMAP YANG modeling. 

Key outcomes included a working group poll regarding the CMOP/SIMAP YANG modeling directions (resulting in strong support to pursue a hybrid use-case-specific approach combining RFC 8345 and RFC 8795), updates on implementation testing from the IETF 126 Hackathon, and initial proposals for collaborating with the Network Management Research Group (NMRG).

