### 6. NMRG and NMOP Collaboration Opportunities
* **Presenter:** Jefferson Capsnobri
* **Slides:** [Network Management Research Group (NMRG) and Network Management Operations (NMOP) Working Group - Collaboration Opportunities](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-nmop-sessa-network-management-research-group-nmrg-and-network-management-operations-nmop-working-group-collaboration-opportunities-00)
* **Discussion:**
  * Jefferson presented opportunities to build stronger bridges between research (IRTF NMRG) and operations (IETF NMOP). Current NMRG focus areas include Intent-Based Networking (IBN), AI in network management, and self-managing networks.
  * Proposed collaboration vectors include sharing internet drafts, joint meetings, and collaborative hackathons.
  * Rob Wilton noted that NMOP is structurally scoped around near-term operational needs (1–2 years), whereas NMRG focuses on a longer horizon (5+ years). He agreed that experiments on how operators deploy AI could bridge the two groups. 
  * Diego Lopez suggested that NMOP should actively look at NMRG research agendas to identify promising experiments to adopt.

