### 8. Model for Distributed Authorization Policy Sharing
* **Presenter:** Lucia Cabanillas
* **Slides:** [Model for distributed authorization policy sharing](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-nmop-sessa-model-for-distributed-authorization-policy-sharing-01)
* **Discussion:**
  * Lucia presented a YANG model designed to distribute authorization policies across heterogeneous policy decision points (PDPs). The policies themselves are written in languages like Rego (Policy-as-Code), while YANG is used to carry the code alongside key metadata.
  * Recent updates include migrating the policy language field to an `identityref` to allow runtime extensions, introducing "author" and "owner" attributes, and defining an "area" leaf to control policy distribution and scope.
  * A Hackathon proof of concept demonstrated successful distribution and enforcement using Open Policy Agent (OPA) and Rego.
  * Mahesh Jethandani asked via chat if this work overlaps with other IETF authorization or policy groups. Lucia replied that this framework is general-purpose and aimed at distributing policies across domains (e.g., to routers or PEPs) rather than competing with specific security policy protocols.

