## Decisions and Action Items

* **CMOP/SIMAP YANG Modeling (Option 4 Poll):**
  * **Decision:** A poll of the room was taken on whether the working group agrees to proceed with Option 4 (using the RFC 8345 approach for generic, non-TE, multi-layer top-down topology and the RFC 8795 approach for traffic engineering and optical use cases, accepting some overlap).
  * **Result:** ~75% of those who voted supported Option 4. This direction will be confirmed on the mailing list.
* **WGLC Planning:**
  * **Decision:** The chairs will initiate WGLC for `draft-ietf-nmop-yang-message-broker-integration` and `draft-ietf-nmop-message-broker-telemetry-message` shortly after the meeting. These documents will be held by the chairs post-WGLC until their external normative dependencies advance.
  * `draft-ietf-nmop-yang-message-broker-message-key` will not be included in this initial WGLC batch, as it was adopted more recently and requires further implementation maturation.

